<body>


  <!-- Main heading for the recipe name -->
  <h1>Spaghetti Carbonara</h1>

  <!-- Paragraph describing the recipe -->
  <p>
    Spaghetti Carbonara is a classic Italian pasta dish made with eggs, cheese, pancetta, and pepper. It's creamy, comforting, and quick to prepare â€” perfect for a delicious weeknight dinner!
  </p>

  <!-- Section heading for the ingredients -->
  <h2>Ingredients</h2>

  <!-- Unordered list for listing ingredients -->
  <ul>
    <li>200g spaghetti</li>
    <li>100g pancetta (or bacon), diced</li>
    <li>2 large eggs</li>
    <li>50g grated Parmesan cheese</li>
    <li>2 cloves garlic, minced (optional)</li>
    <li>Salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste</li>
  </ul>

  <!-- Section heading for the cooking method -->
  <h2>Method</h2>

  <!-- Ordered list for the step-by-step method -->
  <ol>
    <li>Bring a large pot of salted water to a boil. Cook the spaghetti until al dente, then drain, reserving 1/2 cup of pasta water.</li>
    <li>While the pasta is cooking, heat a pan over medium heat and cook the pancetta until crispy. Add garlic if using and cook for 1 minute more.</li>
    <li>In a bowl, whisk the eggs and mix in the grated Parmesan cheese.</li>
    <li>Once the pasta is drained, quickly add it to the pan with the pancetta, tossing to combine.</li>
    <li>Remove the pan from heat and slowly stir in the egg and cheese mixture, adding a little reserved pasta water to create a creamy sauce.</li>
    <li>Season with black pepper and more cheese if desired. Serve immediately.</li>
  </ol>

</body>
